  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing Diverse Voices in Lebanon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ADVIL is a two-year project, funded by the Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs, that aims to strengthen Lebanese media in their role to protect and promote democracy, human rights and fundamental freedoms.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The specific objective of the project is to improve the access of audiences to inclusive and diverse high-quality content in Lebanon by strengthening the editorial and institutional capacity and sustainability of emerging independent media platforms and engaging women and youth in community-based reporting.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, Internews and Maharat will target emerging local, independent media initiatives and women and youth from under-served communities. The final beneficiaries of the project will be the wider population of Lebanon, in particular marginalised voices outside the capital.</narrative>
  </description>
